\begin_layout Standard
In order to simplify notations, again, in physics or mechanics it is generally
 assumed that a comma 
\begin_inset Formula $(,)$
\end_inset

 in a math expression indicates differentiation, usually with respect to
 coordinate 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 as in the following expressions:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u_{i,i}=\frac{\partial u_{i}}{\partial x_{i}}=\sum_{i=1}^{3}\frac{\partial u_{i}}{\partial x_{i}};\qquad u_{i,jj}=\frac{\partial^{2}u_{i}}{\partial x_{j}\partial x_{j}}=\sum_{j=1}^{3}\frac{\partial^{2}u_{i}}{\partial x_{j}^{2}};\qquad A_{ij,j}=\frac{\partial A_{ij}}{\partial x_{j}}=\sum_{j=1}^{3}\frac{\partial A_{ij}}{\partial x_{j}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

